"title": "7330: chief priests",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7330",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A group of individuals in charge of temple worship in Jerusalem, and regarded as leading representatives of the Jewish people, who came into conflict with Jesus Christ and plotted his death.</p>\n<h2>OT references to the chief priest</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:11\">2CH 19:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:18\">2KI 25:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:24\">JER 52:24</a> <em>Seraiah</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:6\">2CH 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:11\">2CH 24:11</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:10\">2CH 31:10</a> <em>Azariah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:5\">EZR 7:5</a> <em>Ezra was descended from Aaron the chief priest</em></p>\n<h2>The chief priests were in charge of temple worship in Jerusalem</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:4\">MAT 2:4</a> <em>They were expected to pronounce on matters of Jewish law and interpretation of Scripture</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:15\">MAT 21:15</a> <em>Temple discipline was their responsibility.</em></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ predicted his suffering at the hands of the chief priests and elders</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:18\">MAT 20:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:33\">MRK 10:33</a></p>\n<h2>The response of the chief priests to Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>They were puzzled by Jesus Christ's teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:23\">MAT 21:23</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:27-Mark11:28\">MRK 11:27–11:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:1-Luke20:2\">LUK 20:1–20:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:45-Matt21:46\">MAT 21:45–21:46</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:19\">LUK 20:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:32\">JHN 7:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:45\">JHN 7:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:47\">JHN 11:47</a> <em>As official representatives of the Jewish people, they feared the political repercussions of Jesus Christ's popularity.</em></p>\n<h3>They and the elders plotted Jesus Christ's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:3-Matt26:5\">MAT 26:3–26:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:1\">MRK 14:1</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:59\">MAT 26:59</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:55\">MRK 14:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:1\">MAT 27:1</a></p>\n<h3>They collaborated with Judas</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:14\">MAT 26:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:10\">MRK 14:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:4\">LUK 22:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:47\">MAT 26:47</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:43\">MRK 14:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:52\">LUK 22:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:3\">JHN 18:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:6\">MAT 27:3–27:6</a></p>\n<h2>The role of the chief priests in the trial of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>They made accusations against Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:12\">MAT 27:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:3\">MRK 15:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:66\">LUK 22:66</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:10\">LUK 23:10</a></p>\n<h3>They persuaded the crowd against Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:20\">MAT 27:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:4\">LUK 23:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:13\">LUK 23:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:6\">JHN 19:6</a></p>\n<h3>They mocked Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:41\">MAT 27:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:31\">MRK 15:31</a></p>\n<h3>They handed Jesus Christ over to Pilate</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:10\">MRK 15:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:20\">LUK 24:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:35\">JHN 18:35</a></p>\n<h3>They persuaded Pilate to have the tomb guarded</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:62-Matt27:66\">MAT 27:62–27:66</a></p>\n<h3>They bribed the soldiers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:11-Matt28:15\">MAT 28:11–28:15</a></p>\n<h3>They rejected Jesus Christ as king</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:15\">JHN 19:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:21\">JHN 19:21</a></p>\n<h2>The chief priests' attempt to prevent the preaching of the gospel</h2>\n<h3>By silencing the apostles</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:23\">ACT 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:24\">ACT 5:24</a></p>\n<h3>By authorising Paul to arrest believers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:14\">ACT 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:21\">ACT 9:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:10\">ACT 26:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:12\">ACT 26:12</a></p>\n<h2>The involvement of the chief priests in the arrest and trial of Paul</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:30\">ACT 22:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:14\">ACT 23:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:2\">ACT 25:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:15\">ACT 25:15</a></p>",
